> With the non-bridged board, each socket will control 2 boards.
> 
> So for board 1, you'll connect to pins 1 and 2 in the socket, and for
> board 2 connect to pins 9 and 10.  The other pins you can do as you please
> (for the brake, current sense, and thermal sense)
